headline: Leidos (LDOS)–CargoSeer Deal: A Fresh Look at Leidos’ Valuation After Its Mezzo Trade-Analysis Integration
summary: Leidos Holdings (LDOS) just gave investors another data point to chew on by teaming up with CargoSeer to plug advanced trade analysis into its Mezzo platform for customs and border agencies. See our latest analysis for Leidos Holdings. That kind of contract momentum, alongside its new CargoSeer tie up, helps explain why Leidos’ share price is sitting around $188.31 after a strong year to date share price return of roughly 31 percent, building on an impressive five year total shareholder...

headline: How Is Leidos Holdings’ Stock Performance Compared to Other Tech Stocks?
summary: Leidos Holdings has outpaced its tech peers over the past year, analysts remain fairly bullish on the stock’s prospects.
